I"I<h1 id="draw-graphnetwork-with-nx_pydot-in-networkx">Draw graph(network) with nx_pydot in networkx</h1>

<p>with ` nx_pydot ` in ` nx.drawing ` , we can have more plotting style of
network/ tree/ graph.</p>

<p>Here is a simple sample:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>import networkx as nx

g=nx.DiGraph()

edgelist = [(0, 1), (1, 12), (2, 12), (3, 17), (4, 11), (5, 4), (6, 10), (7, 12), (8, 14), (9, 14), (10, 11),
            (11, 14), (12, 11), (13, 17), (14, -1), (15, -1), (16, 10), (17, 11), (18, -1)]

g.add_edges_from(edgelist)
p=nx.drawing.nx_pydot.to_pydot(g)
p.write_png('pydot_Tree.png')
</code></pre></div></div>

